parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Front Passenger Air Bag Occupancy Sensor Mat Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front passenger air bag occupancy sensor mat can cause the air bag to disable, increasing the risk of injury or death to the passenger in the event of a crash.
symptoms: The air bag warning light illuminates
the passenger restraint system warning message appears
the passenger air bag is disabled
and the seat belt tensioner or force limiter is affected.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failures can cause fires, loss of vehicle control, and accidents, posing a significant risk to vehicle occupants and other road users.
symptoms: Smoke or flames from the engine compartment
trunk
or headlights; burning odor; electrical shorts; headlights
airbags
or other systems malfunctioning; battery drain; and failure to start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Headlight wiring failures can cause intermittent or complete loss of headlights, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-visibility conditions.
symptoms: Headlights malfunctioning or failing; exposed wiring; insulation flaking off; wires shorting or arcing; and potential fire hazard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Airbag system failures can cause accidents or injuries due to malfunctioning or non-deployment of airbags in the event of a crash.
symptoms: Passenger airbag light remaining on; airbag sensor malfunctioning; and potential failure to deploy airbags in a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Computer and electronic system malfunctions can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, or other safety issues.
symptoms: Speedometer
radio
or other electronic systems malfunctioning; navigation display rebooting; and computer drawing down battery power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Battery and alternator issues can cause loss of vehicle power, stalling, or accidents.
symptoms: Battery drain; alternator warning indicator illuminating; and power failure without warning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake vacuum pump can cause the brake pedal to become hard to press, leading to a loss of power assist braking, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal is hard to press
the brake pedal travels to the floorboard
the vehicle takes longer to stop
the brakes fail to engage
the vehicle vibrates when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake booster can cause the brake pedal to become hard to press, leading to a loss of power assist braking, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal is hard to press
the brake pedal travels to the floorboard
the vehicle takes longer to stop
the brakes fail to engage
the vehicle vibrates when braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake lines can cause a loss of brake fluid, leading to a loss of braking power, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Brake fluid leaks
brake lines rust through
vehicle is difficult to stop.
